args: We're about to lose the sun.
Commander! Enemy troops are\napproaching from the cliffside path!
They're also moving up the mountain\npath on the other side of the camp!\nWe can't possibly hold them all off!
Destroy the path by the cliffs.\nForce them onto the mountain path.
Cover the mountain path in stones just\nlarge enough to impede their march.
Move the injured deeper into the base.\nWe'll reduce our perimeter and tighten\nour defenses.
(The wolf's jaws close around us.\nShould I have ignored the rescue?)
(...No. Defending this base is meaningless\nif the only hope for lasting peace is lost.)
(There was never a real choice here.)
Get back! I'll take your place!
D-damn it all... There's so many of 'em!
It all comes down to this moment.\nTime for me to join the front lines!
Stay back, Commander!\nI'll go in your stead!
Not with those wounds. Stay here, soldier.\nI will command the front directly.
Commander?! I mean, yes, ma'am!\nAll forces, to me!
Damn! The tides are turning...\nFall back! Fall baaack!
(We've held them off, but fatigue\nis starting to take its toll.)
(If Joachim and the others\ncan just return in time...)
I'll confirm the report, ma'am!\nWait, is that...?
...Ma'am, it's a Barthe soldier.\nThese are ENEMY reinforcements.
They've got MORE soldiers?!\nOh, we're done for! It's all over!
(Perhaps I've seen my last sun this day.)
(Still, we will fight to the last.)
Fight on, all of you! Let them taste fear!\nLet them know sorrow! Let the very name\nof Svenitla haunt them to their graves!
Then the base is nearly ours!
Er, wait. Hang on. I actually don't\nremember calling FOR reinforcements.\nWhat unit are you with, anyway?
Damn. This armor sure ain't light.
Well, that seems a bit harsh.\nRegardless, it's time to exact revenge!
Commander! The enemy is breaking rank!\nIt's a full-on mutiny!
Oh, of course! It's Joachim!\nHa! Well played, you old dog!\nStill, I can't let you steal our glory.
Hear me, men! Our ally's sneak attack\nhas thrown the enemy into disarray!
Victory is within our reach!\nWe must endure!
We did it, Commander!\nThe enemy is retreating!
Closer than I'd like, but yes.
Joachim! Was the rescue a success?
All thanks to Joachim's strategy, ma'am!
Oh? Tell me of this strategy.
Joachim snuck into their encampment\ndisguised as a Barthe soldier!
He tricked their captain into moving the\nhostages to a safer location, and we\nmoved them all the way out of camp! Ha!
You've done well to return in one piece.\nI commend your bravery.
Remain resolute, all of you!\nReinforcements are nearly here!
